Some of the Ashborn who emerged from the Cinderteeth eruption's ashfall made their way to the delta settlements before Kowloon was founded.
They arrived in proto-Kowloon's surviving villages as refugees whose physical transformation was not yet understood and not yet named.
The founding houses of Kowloon had more experience with volcanic refugees than Midgaard did: the delta had absorbed people fleeing the Cinderteeth foothills through routes that bypassed Midgaard entirely.
Kowloon's registry, when it was established under the Neon Covenant, created separate designation categories for volcanic-origin refugees rather than forcing them into a human-subtype classification.
This practical decision — driven by the founding houses' familiarity with the actual populations — is why Kowloon has a functioning Ashborn civic registration pathway that Midgaard's intake system still lacks.
The Courier Lantern Office's early census records include Ashborn registration entries predating Midgaard's first Ashborn population documentation by several decades.
Kowloon's Ashborn community is small but formally registered; Midgaard's Ashborn population remains classified under human-subtype designations in the official registry.
